riginally a short form of various compound names containing the word <i>volk</i> ‘people, tribe’ (compare modern English <i>folk</i>). It has gradually died out of general use, but is still used in certain families, in particular the Grevilles. Fulke Greville, 1st Baron Brooke, was a leading figure at the court of Elizabeth I.  See also  Greville ."],"variants":[{"name":"Fulke","meanings":["Of Germanic origin, introduced to Britain by the Normans. The name was originally a short form of various compound names containing the word <i>volk</i> ‘people, tribe’ (compare modern English <i>folk</i>). It has gradually died out of general use, but is still used in certain families, in particular the Grevilles. Fulke Greville, 1st Baron Brooke, was a leading figure at the court of Elizabeth I.  See also  Greville ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Faulk de Braie was born in 1154, in Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Lovel de Braie, was 16 and his mother, Basilia, was 11151. He had at least 1 daughter with Margaret FitzGerold."},"et":{"1154–":"1154–Surnud","1154–Male":"1154–Surnud","1160–Female":"1160–Surnud","1179–Female":"1179–Surnud","1138–Male":"1138–Surnud","1141–Female":"1141–Surnud","1138":"1138","1179":"1179","1154":"1154","1141":"1141","1160":"1160","Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Oakley, Oxfordshire, Eng.":"Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1154–":"1154–Kuollut","1154–Male":"1154–Kuollut","1160–Female":"1160–Kuollut","1179–Female":"1179–Kuollut","1138–Male":"1138–Kuollut","1141–Female":"1141–Kuollut","1138":"1138","1179":"1179","1154":"1154","1141":"1141","1160":"1160","Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Oxfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Oakley, Oxfordshire, Eng.":"Oxfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1154–":"1154–Décédé","1154–Male":"1154–Décédé","1160–Female":"1160–Décédée","1179–Female":"1179–Décédée","1138–Male":"1138–Décédé","1141–Female":"1141–Décédée